SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Japanese student was killed when she was struck by a hit-and-run driver as 
she crossed a street in Scripps Miramar Ranch, police said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was identified as Naoko Shimazu, 20. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred in the 9800 block of Carroll Canyon Road Sunday night, 
said Detective Chuck Vermillion of the San Diego Police Department's traffic 
division. 
</P>
<P>
"She was crossing with a friend, and he got to the other side and turned around 
in time to see her get struck," Vermillion said, who added that the woman was 
not using a crosswalk. 
</P>
<P>
Shimazu, who was pronounced dead at Scripps Memorial Hospital in La Jolla, was 
studying English as a second language at ES International School of English, a 
private school on the United States International University campus. She had 
just completed her two-week program Saturday, said Brigitte McCarthy, director 
of the school. 
</P>
<P>
Police, who have no suspects, are looking for a blue car that may have 
front-end damage on the right side. 
</P>
