SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: RANCHO BERNARDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 25-year-old man accused of running a methamphetamine laboratory out of his 
home was ordered Monday to stand trial in Superior Court. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly C. Schwartz of Rancho Bernardo is charged with manufacturing 
methamphetamine and possession of the drug with the intent to distribute. 
</P>
<P>
Schwartz is in custody in lieu of $250,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
An undercover agent with the Narcotics Task Force testified that a search 
warrant was served at Schwartz's residence July 8. The officer said a working 
methamphetamine lab was found in the attic above the garage. 
</P>
<P>
Schwartz eluded arrest the day the warrant was served. He was apprehended Aug. 
7 in Poway. 
