<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CHIROPRACTOR BEGINS TERM FOR BILLING SCAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Los Angeles chiropractor who pleaded no contest to 14 felony and tax fraud 
charges in a phony billing scheme that bilked insurance companies out of more 
than $400,000 has begun serving a five-year prison sentence. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Albert MacKenzie said Theodore Roosevelt Wyatt conspired 
with some of his patients over a three-year period to submit fraudulent bills 
to their insurance companies, then divided the proceeds with them. 
</P>
<P>
More than 200 patients helped Wyatt prepare false insurance claims for 
non-existent treatment, investigators said. Wyatt paid some his patients $50 
finders fees to recruit others for the scheme. 
</P>
