<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
NOISE DISPUTE LEADS TO SHOOTING ARREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Simi Valley man, annoyed by noise from a neighbor's house, was arrested after 
he fired shots at the neighbor and his friend, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Ronald Wright, 52, was being held in the Ventura County Jail on suspicion of 
assault with a deadly weapon, a jail spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Bail was set at $10,000. 
</P>
<P>
Lt. Neal Rein of the Simi Valley Police Department said Wright was angered by 
noise that his neighbor, Bruce Anthony, was making while working on a car about 
9:40 p.m. Sunday. Wright walked over to Anthony's house and the two began 
arguing, Rein said. 
</P>
<P>
Wright then pulled out a handgun and fired several rounds at Anthony and 
Anthony's friend, Ernst Stirnkorb, 67, Rein said. 
</P>
<P>
Both Anthony and Stirnkorb fled. Neither was injured, Rein said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
