<TEXT>
<P>
Airlines Will Meet to Discuss Fuel Costs: The world's major airlines will 
convene in Geneva next week to discuss whether to charge more because of higher 
fuel costs caused by the Persian Gulf crisis. The meeting, Aug. 29-31, was 
called by the International Air Transport Assn, a group of 191 scheduled 
airlines, to decide on a unified strategy as rising oil prices inflate fuel 
bills that make up 15% of operating costs. Crude oil is trading above $27 a 
barrel, compared to about $15 in June. 
</P>
