<TEXT>
<P>
Steel Can Recycling Increases: The recycling rate shot up more than 39% for 
beverage cans made from steel bodies and aluminum lids, the Steel Can Recycling 
Institute of Pittsburgh reported. More than 700 million cans have been recycled 
so far this year. Many beverage producers are converting to steel, said the 
institute, because they are easily sorted with magnets for recycling and can be 
reprocessed efficiently in steel mills. 
</P>
