<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082190-0059 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 264783 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 21, 1990, Tuesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 7B; Column 5 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
63 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Blue Cross of California named H.W. (Pete) Marston to the newly created post of 
executive vice president for group services, in which he will oversee the 
Woodland Hills-based health insurer's group insurance programs. 
</P>
<P>
Marston previously was senior vice president in charge of group life, health 
and special risk programs at The Hartford, an insurance unit of ITT Corp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
