<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: SEMTECH TAKES STEPS TO BUY ELECTRONICS FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Semtech Corp., a Newbury Park semiconductor maker, said it signed a letter of 
intent with Lambda Electronics Inc. to purchase the assets of Lambda 
Semiconductors in Corpus Christi, Tex., and Reynosa, Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
Terms were not disclosed, but Semtech said the division had $7 million in sales 
in the latest fiscal year and has historically operated at a loss. 
</P>
<P>
Semtech said it expects to complete the transaction within 30 days, but that 
the deal is conditional upon the execution of a definitive agreement. 
</P>
<P>
The Texas facility employs 100 workers and houses the division's semiconductor 
testing, engineering and marketing operations. The semiconductors are assembled 
at the Mexico plant, which has 40 employees. 
</P>
