<P>
UPS Cited for Job Safety Violations: The government proposed $280,000 in fines 
against United Parcel Service for failing to notify the Occupational Safety and 
Health Administration about a job-related death and failing to record more than 
100 other injuries and illnesses. 
</P>
<P>
UPS also failed to record the number of lost workdays caused by the injuries, 
the agency said. OSHA said the alleged violations took place at the company's 
Watertown, Conn., facility. A spokesman for UPS, the nation's largest package 
delivery company, said there would be no immediate comment. 
</P>
