<P>
Interco Announces Restructuring Details: The footwear and furniture maker will 
ask its bondholders to exchange their bonds for 95% of the company's common 
stock and other consideration under a complicated restructuring plan. The plan 
is designed to restructure the $1.9-billion debt that has plagued the St. 
Louis-based company for the past two years. It calls for the company to 
undertake a 23.5-for-1 reverse stock split of Interco's roughly 38.7 million 
shares of common stock, issue 98 million new shares of stock and take on $202 
million in new debt. 
</P>
