<P>
Paycheck Didn't Pay: The U.S. Attorney's Office in Columbus, Ohio, filed a 
civil complaint Monday to collect more than $1.6 million in federal tax 
assessments against imprisoned country music singer Johnny Paycheck. 
</P>
<P>
The government's complaint alleges unpaid tax assessments for the years 
1980-82. Paycheck, 52, whose real name is Donald Lytle, was convicted last year 
in Highland County, Ohio, of aggravated assault and tampering with evidence in 
connection with a barroom shooting. Best known for his hit song "Take This Job 
and Shove It," Paycheck is serving a 7-to-9 1/2-year sentence in Ohio. BETH 
KLEID 
