<TEXT>
<P>
HOT &amp; COLD: "The Two Jakes" may be fading at the box office, but 
"Chinatown," the movie to which "Jakes" is a sequel, is the hottest title in 
local video rentals. 
</P>
<P>
The video has been out for 11 years, but now rental waiting lists are up to a 
week long in some county outlets and new cassettes are on back order. "We only 
have two copies, but those two are consistently off the shelves,' said a clerk 
at a Wherehouse in Santa Ana. "A lot of customers are coming in and asking for 
it since 'The Two Jakes' opened." Jeffrey Perlman and Len Hall 
