<TEXT>
<P>
OptimumCare Corp.: The Laguna Niguel operator of psychiatric care and chemical 
dependency programs reported a net loss of $231,402 for the second quarter, 
compared to a year-earlier loss of $71,091. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue declined 25% to $288,989 from $383,088. For the first half of 1990, the 
company lost $288,978, compared to a loss of $27,545 for the corresponding 
period in 1989. Revenue fell 26% to $646,501 from $873,948. 
