WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
NO FREEDOM FOR CEAUSESCU SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SIBIU, Romania 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A military tribunal hearing genocide charges against Nicu Ceausescu, son of 
executed Romanian dictator Nicolae Ceausescu, refused a defense request today 
to release him from jail because of deteriorating health. 
</P>
<P>
Ceausescu is said to be suffering from hepatitis, cirrhosis of the liver and 
other ailments. 
</P>
<P>
He pleaded innocent to charges he ordered security forces in Sibiu to open fire 
on demonstrators during the December revolution while he was Communist Party 
chief in the region. 
</P>
<P>
More than 90 people died during the fighting. During his trial, Ceausescu said 
the alleged order was a throwaway remark made while he was drunk that he 
retracted when he sobered up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
