<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
SEMANTICS CLASS LOSES 'F WORD' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EVANSVILLE, Ind. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The "F word" has been eliminated from the curriculum at Evansville Central High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
The Evansville-Vanderburgh School Board, in a 5-2 vote, ordered teacher Jim 
Wooten today to stop using the four-letter vulgarity for sexual intercourse in 
his class on semantics. 
</P>
<P>
Wooten has taught the course for 15 years. Students and parents at Evansville 
Central were warned in advance that a segment of the three-month elective deals 
with profanity. 
</P>
<P>
A school curriculum committee, responding to a complaint from a parent, ordered 
Wooten to stop using the word several weeks ago. Wooten appealed to the school 
board. 
</P>
</TEXT>
