<HEADLINE>
<P>
NELSON TO FACE LAPORTE IN TITLE DEFENSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SYDNEY, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Azumah Nelson will defend his World Boxing Council super featherweight title 
against Juan LaPorte of Puerto Rico at the Sydney Entertainment Center on Oct. 
13, promoter Bill Mordey announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Mordey said the winner of the fight, which has been switched from Sept. 7 at 
Nelson's request, will fight Australian three-time world champion Jeff Fenech 
in Sydney in February. 
</P>
<P>
Mordey said he has signed a two-fight deal with American promoter Don King 
worth $1.6 million and said he will co-promote both bouts with King. 
</P>
<P>
Nelson relinquished the title earlier this year to challenge Pernell Whitaker 
of the United States for the WBC lightweight crown. He lost a decision to 
Whitaker. 
</P>
<P>
LaPorte and Fenech were slated to meet for the vacant title, but the unbeaten 
Australian has twice withdrawn with a viral infection. 
</P>
<P>
"The WBC has said it still recognizes Nelson as champion, so he will defend 
against LaPorte with the winner to face Fenech," Mordey said. 
</P>
